        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Barcelona</placeName> <date>Decr. 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Is. Leeser Esqr.</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadpa.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Revd. Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">As I am about retiring from this part of <placeName>America</placeName><lb/> during the ensuing month of <date>Janry.</date>&#44; I must beg you to hasten<lb/> the remittance of the Books ordered &#38; at the same time request<lb/> you to draw at <hi rend="underline">eight days</hi> sight for their import&#44; in favor of<lb/> <persName>Messrs A. M. Seixas &#38; Co.</persName> of <placeName>LaGuaira</placeName>. Please send also the<lb/> bill of their <sic>seperate</sic> costs.</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Your last letter reached me just on the point of<lb/> Leaving this for <placeName><sic>curacao</sic></placeName> &#38; was extremely sorry that it also reached<lb/> me so late in the season &#38; thereby preventing me from remitting<lb/> you the <add>Hebrew</add> asked for&#59; but should your expected letter arrive<lb/> in time &#38; should you still required them&#44; I shall then endeavor<lb/> in time &#38; should you still require them&#44; I shall then endeavor<lb/> forward you some either by way of <placeName>LaGuaira</placeName>&#44; <placeName>St Thos</placeName> or direct.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">In haste I remain Revd Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Saml Piza</persName></p>
			<p>PS. Please include the amt. I owe for the Occident in the bill<lb/> drawn in favor of <persName>Messrs A. M Seixas &#38; Co.</persName> &#38; cease sending after the<lb/> month. <hi rend="underline">vale</hi></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>Forwarded by <persName>D <add>&#63;</add> S</persName></p>
          
        </body>
